16821, "Moteurs"

16822, "GTF Kulas"

16823, "(fr)Space Superiority"

16824, "(fr)High"

16825, "(fr)RNI Systems"

16826, "(fr)The GTF Kulas is a light fighter in active deployment in the GTVA Navy. The Kulas existed as a paramilitary light fighter long before the conception of the Threat Exigency Initiative, but the deployment of the fighter into the front lines is officially recognised as the incipient event of the TEI's Wave One program.

In the aftermath of the Second Shivan Incursion, the GTVA fleet was exhausted and demoralised. High Command authorised a crash program to restock the Terran fighter corps as part of the first steps towards rebuilding the GTVA navy. Utilising a venerable but versatile paramilitary spaceframe, RNI Systems spearheaded the modernisation of the Kulas and began bulk production of the light fighter. With an overpowered reactor, the Kulas has good power efficiency, excellent afterburner capacity and superb maneuverability. However, its secondary capacity is lacking, and its single four-gun bank has proven somewhat undergunned for the demands of the Sol theater."

16827, "14,5 m"

16828, "GTF Atalante"

16829, "(fr)The Atalanta is the first of the Threat Exigency Initiative's Wave 2 fighters, true next-generation strike craft with extraordinary capabilities. Produced in record time by the Alliance's first wholly classified procurement and design process - plagued by rumors of intrigue and mysterious 'red assets' - the Atalanta is an elegant, minimalist design wholly devoted to murdering other strike craft with very nearly Shivan flight characteristics. The original specifications of the Atalanta called for a multirole interceptor and space superiority fighter. Due to the United Earth Federation's fighter corps' successes, this variant has been field-modified to enhance its capabilities in the space-superiority role. These fighters remain rare in the Terran theatre, but they are likely to become a mainstay of Alliance forces in the near future."

16830, "17 m"

16831, "GTF Nyx"

16832, "Assaut Lourd/Supériorité Spatiale"

16833, "(fr)Heavy"

16834, "Tueur de Canonnières dédié"

16835, "Issu de la deuxième vague de chasseurs de l'Initiative d'Urgence contre les Menaces, le GTF Nyx est l'un des derniers chasseurs lourds de la GTVA, se situant entre la niche de l'assaut lourd multirôle/supériorité spatiale et le concept vasudien de chasseur de domination spatiale. Sa conception a été accélérée en 2385 en réponse à l'augmentation des pertes de chasseurs par rapport aux chasseurs de conception supérieure de l'UEF. Ce chasseur est devenu le fléau de nombreux pilotes de l'UEF, grâce à son blindage lourd et à sa puissance de feu. Il combine les huit batteries de canons de l'Érinyes avec l'agilité et la polyvalence de l'intercepteur Persée, produisant ainsi un modèle exceptionnel qui est devenu le préféré des pilotes. Son cout exorbitant a toutefois ralenti son déploiement initial."

16836, "GTF Draco"

16837, "(fr)Interceptor"

16838, "Triton Dynamics/Nankam Aéronautique"

16839, "(fr)Analysis of defensive actions during the Second Incursion, such as the evacuation of Third Fleet Headquarters in Capella, revealed systemic failures in defensive fighter coverage. Multi-axis attack by lightly escorted Shivan bombers demanded rapid redeployment across kilometers of space, and in terms of pure linear speed, no Terran fighter design was up to the challenge. When the Threat Exigency Initiative was launched, one of the first demands of the GTVA admiralty was for a new dedicated fighter design in the pure intercept role, a tactical niche left empty since the retirement of the GTF Valkyrie in 2361. Its stunning speed and fast recharge drive capacitors quickly made it a pilot favorite. 

Evaluation did not complete in time for the departure of the 14th Battlegroup, and GTVA Command further held back its deployment to the Sol theater for fear that it would be easy prey for UEF point defenses and the heavier Kentauroi. While it remains a rare sight, these concerns were largely unfounded. Thanks to a doctrine of evasion and attack by pure speed, the Draco now enjoys one of the highest kill/casualty ratios of any Alliance strikecraft in the conflict. Though arguably undergunned when attacking heavier UEF strike craft, the Draco nonetheless exerts a powerful tactical presence."

